    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-02-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-02-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="83"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d83">
                <head>83. National Security Action Memorandum No. 221<note n="0" type="source"
                        xml:id="d83fn0">Source: <persName corresp="#p_KJF2">Kennedy</persName>
                        Library, National Security Files, Meetings and Memoranda Series, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSAM1">NSAM</gloss>s, <gloss target="#t_NSAM1"
                        >NSAM</gloss>-21. Secret. A copy was sent to the Director of the Bureau of
                        the Budget.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1963-02-20">February 20, 1963</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>MEMORANDUM TO</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Defense</item>
                    <item>The Director of Central Intelligence</item>
                    <item>The Administrator, Agency for International Development</item>
                    <item>The Director, United States Information Agency</item>
                    <item>The Director, Peace Corps</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>U.S. Policy Toward Algeria</item>
                </list>
                <p>I generally approve the Plan of Action for Algeria in the Secretary of State’s
                    memorandum to me of 2 February 1963, responding to <gloss target="#t_NSAM1"
                        >NSAM</gloss> 211.<note n="1" xml:id="d83fn1">
                        <ref target="#d81">Document 81</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>All concerned should bear in mind the need for a program commensurate with our
                    policy interests in this key North African country. While we want France to
                    shoulder the lion’s share of the burden, we also want to increase our own
                    influence. For example, I should like to be advised if it should appear highly
                    desirable to exceed somewhat the $15 million <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss>
                    1964 <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss> level currently projected.</p>
                <p>Since Prime Minister <persName>Ben Bella</persName> has requested assistance from
                    the Peace Corps and the Algerians need just the sort of help the Peace Corps is
                    peculiarly suited to give, I hope it will be able to respond if other
                    commitments permit.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KJF2">
                            <hi rend="strong">John F. Kennedy</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
